{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:12:23.992653+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"issues\":[{\"number\":1,\"title\":\"gif profile output looks washed out / banded compared to other tools\",\"body\":\"I\\u0026#39;m running `vidpack gif clip.mp4` to convert short screen recordings to GIFs for chat. The output works but the color quality is noticeably worse than what I get with a manual ffmpeg two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline, or with tools like gifski.\\n\\nSteps to reproduce:\\n  1. Take any short mp4 with reasonably saturated colors\\n  2. Run: vidpack gif clip.mp4\\n  3. Compare resulting clip.gif against gifski --quality 90\\n\\nExpected: roughly comparable color quality\\nActual: noticeable banding, particularly in gradients\\n\\nLooks like vidpack\\u0026#39;s gif profile is doing single-pass conversion without generating a palette first. Is that intentional, or should the gif profile switch to a two-pass approach?\\n\\nvidpack version: 0.1.0\\nffmpeg version: 6.0\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\"},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T00:49:27Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T00:49:27Z\"}],\"totalCount\":1,\"pageInfo\":{\"hasNextPage\":false,\"hasPreviousPage\":false,\"startCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMDo0OToyN1rPAAAAAQwng2A=\",\"endCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMDo0OToyN1rPAAAAAQwng2A=\"}}", "id": "lc_0663db55-850d-4fc6-a1ba-7f440f9aac2e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "list_issues", "id": "d0e33965-df0a-440f-a884-8b221a81ea8a", "tool_call_id": "call_00_HpDPBSNC1jAMyrrOpIwt3362", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
