{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:12:52.346872+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 522, "prompt_tokens": 8697, "total_tokens": 9219, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 153, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8576}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 8576, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 121}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "e09d0a10-1d2a-4a28-82bf-dba3e6d916b0", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea425-41da-7800-8ca4-1e64194b0212-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thanks for the report @BruceKZ — this is a known limitation already acknowledged in the codebase.\n\nThe `[gif]` profile in `profiles.toml` has the following note:\n\n> *\"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\"*\n\nAnd in `src/vidpack/runner.py` (line 14–17), the GIF path is intentionally a single-pass filter chain (`fps=...,scale=...`) with a comment referencing the same trade-off. The single-pass approach was chosen for simplicity and speed (no temp files, one ffmpeg invocation), but as you've observed it leads to banding and washed-out gradients compared to a proper two-pass `palettegen`/`paletteuse` pipeline or dedicated tools like gifski.\n\nSwitching the gif profile to a two-pass approach would be the right fix. It would require:\n- Generating a palette file in a first pass (`palettegen`)\n- Using that palette in a second pass (`paletteuse`)\n- Handling temporary file cleanup\n\nI'm leaving this open to track the enhancement. PRs welcome if anyone wants to tackle it."}, "id": "call_00_i0sSeawcxx47gKTi3EMc2715", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8697, "output_tokens": 522, "total_tokens": 9219, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 8576}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 153}}}}]}}}
